machine_end_gcode:
; ### Required End-Print-macro for the Klipper Printer Additions": Cleans up state, presents the print, moves head higher up, turn off extruder, bed, motors, fan. ###
_End_Print

; ### Optional call to "Christian Vick's Klipper Printer Additions": Let the external part fan run to cool the build plate fast. Set the build plate with the model vertically on the bed, and let the fan blow on it. Quite handy if you print in a row, or for impatient people. :-) ###
; ### If you want to use this, remove the ";" from the beginning of the next line: ###
;Fan_Part_Aux_Timer SECONDS=180 SPEED=50  ;### This is for Printer Addtions v2.5 and higher. ###


; ### Alternatively, the standard end-print macro in printer.cfg ###
; ### If you want to use this, remove the ";" from the next line, and disable the KPA-macro at the top: ###
;END_PRINT
machine_start_gcode:
; ### hack-fix to generate preview-images in Moonraker / fluidd / printer's display: Write fake slicer info here so that preprocess_cancellation can process. Do not remove the ";". ###
; generated by SuperSlicer 1.7.0 on 2024-01-03 at 00:00:00

; ### Calling the pre-print-macro of the Klipper Printer Additions.
; ### https://www.printables.com/model/585691
; ### Takes care of G2/3/17 errors, first layer consistency, speed heating, multi-mesh, adaptive mesh / priming ###
; ### If you don't want to use this, for some strange reason ;), add a ";" at the beginning of the next line: ####
_Pre_Print_Procedure BED_TEMP=[bed_temperature_initial_layer_single] EXTRUDER_TEMP=[nozzle_temperature_initial_layer] CHAMBER_TEMP=[chamber_temperature] AREA_START={first_layer_print_min[0]},{first_layer_print_min[1]} AREA_END={first_layer_print_max[0]},{first_layer_print_max[1]} LAYER_C=[total_layer_count] LAYER_H=[layer_height] FILA_TYPE=[filament_type] NOZ_DIA={nozzle_diameter[0]}
M140 S[bed_temperature_initial_layer_single] ; Let the Power failure Resume feature pickup the temperature.
M104 S[nozzle_temperature_initial_layer]         ; Let the Power failure Resume feature pickup the temperature.

; ### Alternatively, the standard pre-print macro in printer.cfg ###
; ### If you want to use this, remove the ";" from the next 3 lines: ####
;M190 S[bed_temperature_initial_layer_single]
;M109 S[nozzle_temperature_initial_layer]
;START_PRINT
